      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1499750310107-5fef28a66643?w=500&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8Mnx8YmxvZ3xlbnwwfHwwfHx8MA%3D%3D" class="img-fluid rounded mb-4" alt="Web Development Trends">
      
      <div class="blog-content">
        <p class="lead">The web development landscape is evolving at an unprecedented pace. As we move forward, several key trends are shaping the future of how we build and interact with web applications.</p>
        
        <h3>AI Integration</h3>
        <p>Artificial Intelligence is no longer a futuristic concept – it's here and transforming web development. From chatbots to personalized user experiences, AI is becoming an integral part of modern web applications.</p>
        
        <h3>Progressive Web Apps (PWAs)</h3>
        <p>PWAs continue to bridge the gap between web and mobile applications, offering native app-like experiences through web browsers. They provide offline functionality, push notifications, and improved performance.</p>
        
        <h3>Serverless Architecture</h3>
        <p>Serverless computing is revolutionizing how we deploy and scale web applications. It allows developers to focus on code rather than infrastructure management, leading to faster development cycles and reduced costs.</p>
        
        <h3>WebAssembly (WASM)</h3>
        <p>WebAssembly is enabling high-performance applications to run in web browsers, opening up new possibilities for complex web applications that were previously only possible with native development.</p>
        
